cadMacMib.name: cadMacMib

revisions.description: Add cadSubmgtFilterGrpDescTable, the Subscriber Management Filter Group Description Table.
Expand the CadArp table to include additional information.
Change syntax of cadEnforceRuleTableLastChange to Counter32.

Add cadEnforceRuleTable cadEnforceRuleCountsTable cadIfCmtsCmStatusDsPenalties cadIfCmtsCmStatusUsPenalties cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyStart cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyDuration cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyStart cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyDuration cadMacClearPenaltyCounts cadMacClearPenaltyCountsByIfIndex cadMacClearPenaltyCountMacAddr cadMacClearPenaltyCountScn
Add cadIfCmtsCmCountsSignalNoise, cadIfCmtsCmCountsUnerroreds, cadIfCmtsCmCountsCorrecteds, and cadIfCmtsCmCountsUncorrectables to cadIfCmtsCmCountsEntry
Change MAX-ACCESS of cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddrType and cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddr from read-only to not-accessible

Add cadSubMgtCpeControlLastReset, cadSubMgtCpeControlMaxCpeIpv6Prefix, cadSubMgtCpeIpAddrType, cadSubMgtPsFilterDownstream, cadSubMgtPsFilterUpstream, cadSubMgtMtaFilterDownstream, cadSubMgtMtaFilterUpstream, cadSubMgtStbFilterDownstream cadSubMgtStbFilterUpstream Change Syntax of cadSubMgtCpeIpMacAddr from IpAddress to InetAddressIPv4or6.
Add initial device classes support from 5.2. Added cadSubMgtCpeCpeType to CadSubMgtCmFilterEntry. Added cadIfCmtsCmStatuseDocsisType to cadIfCmtsCmStatusEntry.
Restrict size of cm vendor name and arp inet address.
Add MIB objects in cadIfCmtsCmStatusTable to support DOCSIS 3.0 and add new enumeration values to CadIfCmtsCmStatusType
Add cadIfCmtsCmCCmDownChannelCount and cadIfCmtsCmCCmUpChannelCount to to cadIfCmtsCmCCmTable
Add cadCmtsCmStatusNumTotal, cadCmtsCmStatusNumActive, and cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistered to cadCmtsCmStatusSummaryTable
Add 64-bit version of cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime and cadIfCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime to prevent large value wrap-around problem.
Add cadMacClearFlapCountMacAddr to clear the flap counts for individual modem
Specify maximum 100 rows in Modem Deny list table.
Modem Deny list feature - add cadMacClearDenyCounts to clear the counts.
Added cadCpeHostAuthorizationTable for CPE Host Authorization (Motorola Style Anti-Spoofing) feature.
Adding objects cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsCapability and cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsProvisioned to deprecate cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisVersion.
Add reverse mapping table for MAC <-> IP/CMMAC translation
Bumping cadCmtsCmVendorTable from cadMacMib.17 to cadMacMib.20.
Included support for TFTP Enforce feature.
Creating cadCmtsCmVendorTable to map OUIs to vendors and vice-versa.
Add flaplist enhancements and placeholder for cmptr.
OSS-N-03068 Deprecate operational(8) and add registeredBPIInitializing(9) for docsIfCmtsCmStatusValue.
Using DocsisVersion from DOCS-IF-MIB rather than from DOCS-IF-EXT-MIB to support 2.0
Adding object to support resetting cable modems from the CMTS.
In response to the draft-05 version of the DOCS-IF-MIB required for cw26, added cadIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType to the cadIfCmtsCmStatusTable.
Add MIB support for interface to MAC DB.

In response to the draft-05 version of the DOCS-IF-MIB required for cw26, added cadCmtsCmStatusNumOperational to CadCmtsCmStatusSummaryEntry and updated CadIfCmtsCmStatusType to add the operational(8) value.
added cadIfCmtsCmStatusConfigFilename, cadIfCmtsCmStatusBpiVersion, and cadIfCmtsCmStatusModemType to CadIfCmtsCmStatusEntry.
added cadSubMgtCpeFilterDownstream and cadSubMgtCpeFilterUpstream to CadSubMgtCpeIpEntry
Created the cadQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowTable with a service flow ID that is read-only. This addresses the problem of the docsQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowTable's service flow ID being not-accessible.
changed cadIfCmtsServiceId from not-accessible to read-only

cadMacMib.contactinfo: Arris Support Postal: ARRIS Phone: +1 770 622 8530 E-mail: support@arris.com
cadMacMib.description: This is the Cadant version of all the tables which are really indexed by MacAddress, but are index by docsIfCmtsCmStatusIndex in the DOCS-IF-MIB

CadIfCmtsCmStatusType.name: CadIfCmtsCmStatusType
CadIfCmtsCmStatusType.description: The current known state of the cable modem.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusNumber.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusNumber
cadIfCmtsCmStatusNumber.description: The number of rows in the cadIfCmtsCmStatusTable

cadIfCmtsCmStatusMacAddress.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusMacAddress
cadIfCmtsCmStatusMacAddress.description: MAC address of this Cable Modem

cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisVersion.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisVersion
cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisVersion.description: Indication whether the CM has registered as a 1.0 or 1.1 modem. This object has been deprecated with the new objects cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsCapability and cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsProvisioned. This object will be removed in a future release.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusRangFlaps.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusRangFlaps
cadIfCmtsCmStatusRangFlaps.description: Number of times the CM has flapped in Ranging states.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusProvFlaps.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusProvFlaps
cadIfCmtsCmStatusProvFlaps.description: Number of times the CM has flapped in Provisioning states.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusRegFlaps.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusRegFlaps
cadIfCmtsCmStatusRegFlaps.description: Number of times the CM has flapped in Registered state.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime
cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime.description: Timestamp of the last time the CM flapped.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime
cadIfCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime.description: Timestamp of the last time the CM did initial ranging.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusPreFlapStatus.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusPreFlapStatus
cadIfCmtsCmStatusPreFlapStatus.description: CM status value prior to last CM flap.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusConfigFilename.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusConfigFilename
cadIfCmtsCmStatusConfigFilename.description: Name of the file used to configure the modem during registration.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusBpiVersion.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusBpiVersion
cadIfCmtsCmStatusBpiVersion.description: The value of this object is the version of Baseline Privacy for which this CM has registered.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusModemType.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusModemType
cadIfCmtsCmStatusModemType.description: The type of modem that has been detected. This value is unknown(0) if the CMTS cannot determine a proper value. The standalone(1) value is set if the modem is a canonical DOCSIS 1.0 or 1.1 modem. The mta(2) value is used if the modem has been detected as being an MTA.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType
cadIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType.reference: DOCSIS Radio Frequency Interface Specification, Table 8-19.
cadIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType.description: Indicates modulation type currently used by the CM. Since this object specifically identifies PHY mode, the shared type is not permitted. If the upstream channel is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusTftpEnforceFailed.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusTftpEnforceFailed
cadIfCmtsCmStatusTftpEnforceFailed.description: Indicates if TFTP Enforce failed during the modem registration.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusDynamicSecretFailed.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusDynamicSecretFailed
cadIfCmtsCmStatusDynamicSecretFailed.description: Indicates if Dynamic Secret failed during the modem registration.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsCapability.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsCapability
cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsCapability.description: The highest DOCSIS version the modem is capable of operating at. Note this comes from the modem itself and not the configuration file.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsProvisioned.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsProvisioned
cadIfCmtsCmStatusDocsProvisioned.description: The DOCSIS version the modem has currently been configured to operate at. Note this comes from the config file and is not based upon the hardware capabilities of the modem.

cadIfHVCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime.name: cadIfHVCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime
cadIfHVCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime.description: The timestamp of the last time the CM flapped, measured in centiseconds. This object is a 64-bit version of cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastFlapTime.

cadIfHVCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime.name: cadIfHVCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime
cadIfHVCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime.description: The timestamp of the last time the CM did initial ranging, measured in centiseconds. This object is a 64-bit version of cadIfCmtsCmStatusInitRangTime.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusIPv6Addr.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusIPv6Addr
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusIPv6Addr.description: This attribute represents the IPv6 address of the CM. If the CM has no Internet address assigned, or the Internet address is unknown, the value of this attribute is the all zeros address.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusIPv6LinkLocal.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusIPv6LinkLocal
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusIPv6LinkLocal.description: This attribute represents the IPv6 local scope address of the CM. If the CM has no link local address assigned, or the Internet address is unknown, the value of this attribute is the all zeros address.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusMdIfIndex.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusMdIfIndex
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusMdIfIndex.description: This attribute represents the interface Index of the CMTS MAC Domain where the CM is active. If the interface is unknown, the CMTS returns a value of zero.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusMdCmSgId.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusMdCmSgId
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusMdCmSgId.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I01-060804, Cable Modem Service Group (CM-SG) section.
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusMdCmSgId.description: This attribute represents the ID of the MAC Domain CM Service Group Id (MD-CM-SG-ID) in which the CM is registered. If the ID is unknown, the CMTS returns a value of zero.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcpId.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcpId
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcpId.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I01-060804, RCP-ID section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcpId.description: This attribute represents the RCP-ID associated with the CM. If the RCP-ID is unknown the CMTS returns a five octet long string of zeros.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRccStatusId.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRccStatusId
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRccStatusId.description: This attribute represents the RCC Id the CMTS used to configure the CM receive channel set during the registration process. If unknown, the CMTS returns the value zero.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcsId.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcsId
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcsId.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I01-060804, Cable Modem Physical Receive Channel Configuration section and the Receive Channels section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusRcsId.description: This attribute represents the Receive Channel Set (RCS) that the CM is currently using. If the RCS is unknown, the CMTS returns the value zero.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusTcsId.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusTcsId
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusTcsId.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I01-060804, Changes to the Transmit Channel Set section.
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusTcsId.description: This attribute represents Transmit Channel Set (TCS) the CM is currently using. If the TCS is unknown, the CMTS returns the value zero.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusLastRegTime.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusLastRegTime
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusLastRegTime.description: This attribute represents the last time the CM registered.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusInetIpAddrType.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusInetIpAddrType
cadIfCmtsCmStatusInetIpAddrType.description: The address type associated with the cable modem's IP address

cadIfCmtsCmStatusInetIpAddress.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusInetIpAddress
cadIfCmtsCmStatusInetIpAddress.description: The IPv4 or IPv6 IP address assigned to the cable modem.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusServiceType.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusServiceType
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusServiceType.description: This attribute denotes the queueing services the CM registered, either DOCSIS 1.1 QoS or DOCSIS 1.0 CoS mode.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusBpiEnabled.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusBpiEnabled
cadIfCmtsCmStatusBpiEnabled.description: This attribute denotes if BPI is enabled on the CM.

cadIfCmtsCmStatuseDocsisTypes.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatuseDocsisTypes
cadIfCmtsCmStatuseDocsisTypes.description: The types of eDOCSIS devices within the modem that have been detected. This list is derived from the vendor specific option (option 43.3) in the DHCP packet from the CM.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusDsPenalties.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusDsPenalties
cadIfCmtsCmStatusDsPenalties.description: Number of times the CM has had a downstream SF penalized. When this count is cleared, Start and Duration will not be reset since this CM may still be in penalty

cadIfCmtsCmStatusUsPenalties.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusUsPenalties
cadIfCmtsCmStatusUsPenalties.description: Number of times the CM has had an upstream SF penalized. When this count is cleared, Start and Duration will not be reset since this CM may still be in penalty

cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyStart.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyStart
cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyStart.description: The timestamp of the most recent time the system started penalizing a downstream SF on that CM.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyDuration.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyDuration
cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastDsPenaltyDuration.description: The duration of the last downstream penalty.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyStart.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyStart
cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyStart.description: The timestamp of the most recent time the system started penalizing an upstream SF on that CM.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyDuration.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyDuration
cadIfCmtsCmStatusLastUsPenaltyDuration.description: The duration of the last upstream penalty.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusRxAcPowerLost.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusRxAcPowerLost
cadIfCmtsCmStatusRxAcPowerLost.description: This attribute denotes if the CMTS believes the CM to be in an AC Power Loss condition.

cadIfCmtsCmStatusInsertionFlaps.name: cadIfCmtsCmStatusInsertionFlaps
cadIfCmtsCmStatusInsertionFlaps.description: Number of times the CM has flapped in Provisioned or Registered state within the flaplist insertion interval.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtCapability.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtCapability
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtCapability.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I20-121113, Energy Management Features section.
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtCapability.description: This attribute indicates the Energy Management Features the CM supports. If this attribute returns em1x1Mode(0) bit set, the CM supports the Energy Management 1x1 feature. If this attribute returns em1x1Mode(0) bit cleared, the CM does not support the Energy Management 1x1 feature. Note: This attribute only indicates if an Energy Management Feature is supported by the CM and does not indicate if the feature is enabled/disabled via the CM config file and registration request/response exchange and and does not indicate whether the CM is actively operation in an Energy Management Mode.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtEnabled.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtEnabled
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtEnabled.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I20-121113, Energy Management Features section.
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtEnabled.description: This attribute indicates which, if any, of the Energy Management Features are enabled for this CM. If this attribute returns em1x1Mode(0) bit set, the CM is configured with the Energy Management 1x1 Feature enabled. If this attribute returns all bits cleared, the CM will not request to operate in any Energy Management mode of operation. Note: This attribute only indicates if an Energy Management Feature is enabled/disabled via the CM config file and registration request/response exchange and does not indicate whether the CM is actively operating in an Energy Management Mode.

cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtOperStatus.name: cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtOperStatus
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtOperStatus.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I20-121113, Energy Management 1x1 Mode Indicator section.
cadIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtOperStatus.description: This attribute indicates whether the CM is currently operating in an Energy Management Mode. If this attribute returns em1x1Mode(0) bit set, the CM is operating in Energy Management 1x1 Mode. If this attribute returns all bits cleared, the CM is not operating in any Energy Management Mode. This attribute always returns 0x00 (no bits set) in the case when docsIf3CmtsCmRegStatusEnergyMgtEnabled is set to 0x00 (no Energy Management Features enabled).

cadIf3CmtsCmStatsEm1x1ModeTotalDuration.name: cadIf3CmtsCmStatsEm1x1ModeTotalDuration
cadIf3CmtsCmStatsEm1x1ModeTotalDuration.description: This attribute indicates the total time duration, in seconds that this CM (identified by docsIf3CmtsCmRegStatusId ) was in Energy Management 1x1 mode, not including the duration of time if it is Currently in Energy Management 1x1 mode as controlled by the DBC-REQ Energy Management 1x1 Mode Indicator TLV.

cadIf3CmtsCmStatsEm1x1ModeEntryTime.name: cadIf3CmtsCmStatsEm1x1ModeEntryTime
cadIf3CmtsCmStatsEm1x1ModeEntryTime.description: This attribute indicates the sysUpTime when the CM started its current Energy Management 1x1 mode cycle, in seconds. Zero indicates the CM is currently not in the Energy Management 1x1 mode.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsRxPower.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsRxPower
cadIfCmtsCmCountsRxPower.description: The reciever power as perceived for upstream data from this cable modem. If the receive power is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsTimingOffset.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsTimingOffset
cadIfCmtsCmCountsTimingOffset.description: A measure of the current round trip time for this cable modem. Used for timing of CM upstream transmissions to ensure synchronized arrivals at the CMTS. Units are in terms of 6.25 microseconds/(64*256). Returns zero if the value is unknown.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsEqualizationData.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsEqualizationData
cadIfCmtsCmCountsEqualizationData.description: Equalization data for this CM. Returns an empty string if the value is unknown or if there is no equalization data available or defined.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsRangeReqOpportunities.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsRangeReqOpportunities
cadIfCmtsCmCountsRangeReqOpportunities.description: The number of ranging request opportunities.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsRangeReqReceived.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsRangeReqReceived
cadIfCmtsCmCountsRangeReqReceived.description: The number of ranging request frames received.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsPowerAdjExceedsThreshol.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsPowerAdjExceedsThreshold
cadIfCmtsCmCountsPowerAdjExceedsThreshol.description: The number of ranging request which results in a power adjustment greater than the threshold value.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsSignalNoise.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsSignalNoise
cadIfCmtsCmCountsSignalNoise.description: This attribute represents Signal/Noise ratio as perceived for upstream data from the CM on this upstream channel.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsUnerroreds.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsUnerroreds
cadIfCmtsCmCountsUnerroreds.description: This attribute represents the codewords received without error from the CM on this interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime for the associated upstream channel.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsCorrecteds.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsCorrecteds
cadIfCmtsCmCountsCorrecteds.description: This attribute represents the codewords received with correctable errors from the CM on this upstream channeli. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime for the associated upstream channel.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsUncorrectables.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsUncorrectables
cadIfCmtsCmCountsUncorrectables.description: This attribute represents the codewords received with uncorrectable errors from the CM on this upstream channel. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the managed system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime for the associated upstream channel.

cadIfCmtsCmCountsTxPower.name: cadIfCmtsCmCountsTxPower
cadIfCmtsCmCountsTxPower.description: This attribute holds the value of CM channel transmit power that is included in the last CM ranging request message (in units of quarter dBmV). This value is updated at the receipt of every station maintenance message. Default value is zero. The value of this MIB object will be non-zero only for D3.0 CMs when MTCM is enabled. If the value of this MIB object is 0, it means that the object is not populated yet or MTCM is disabled (or both).

cadIfCmtsServiceMacAddress.name: cadIfCmtsServiceMacAddress
cadIfCmtsServiceMacAddress.description: MAC address of the Cable Modem this SID is associated with.

cadIfCmtsServiceQosProfile.name: cadIfCmtsServiceQosProfile
cadIfCmtsServiceQosProfile.description: This should be 1 if this is the default flow.

cadIfCmtsPtrToMacTable.name: cadIfCmtsPtrToMacTable
cadIfCmtsPtrToMacTable.description: This table is the inverse of docsIfCmtsMacToCmTable

cadIfCmtsCmPtr.name: cadIfCmtsCmPtr
cadIfCmtsCmPtr.description: An row index into the docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable.

cadIfCmtsCmMac.name: cadIfCmtsCmMac
cadIfCmtsCmMac.description: The MAC address this CMPtr is for.

cadSubMgtCpeControlTable.name: cadSubMgtCpeControlTable
cadSubMgtCpeControlTable.description: This table extends the cadifCmtsCmStatusTable and adds 4 objects which reflect the state of subscriber management on a particular CM.

cadSubMgtCpeControlMaxCpeIpv6Addresses.name: cadSubMgtCpeControlMaxCpeIpv6Addresses
cadSubMgtCpeControlMaxCpeIpv6Addresses.description: This attribute represents the number of simultaneous IPv6 prefixes permitted ofr CPE connected to the CM.

cadSubMgtCpeControlLastReset.name: cadSubMgtCpeControlLastReset
cadSubMgtCpeControlLastReset.description: This attribute represents the system Up Time of the last set to 'true' of the Reset attribute of this instance. Zero if never reset.

cadSubMgtCpeIpEntry.name: cadSubMgtCpeIpEntry
cadSubMgtCpeIpEntry.description: An entry in the cadSubMgtCpeIpTable. The first index is the specific modem we're referring to, the second index is the IP address of a specific CPE.

cadSubMgtCpeIpLearned.name: cadSubMgtCpeIpLearned
cadSubMgtCpeIpLearned.description: TRUE if this IP addresses was learned, FALSE if it was provisioned

cadSubMgtCpeIpMacAddr.name: cadSubMgtCpeIpMacAddr
cadSubMgtCpeIpMacAddr.description: The MAC address of this CPE.

cadSubMgtCpeFilterDownstream.name: cadSubMgtCpeFilterDownstream
cadSubMgtCpeFilterDownstream.description: This is the per-CPE equivalent of docsSubMgtSubFilterDownstream

cadSubMgtCpeFilterUpstream.name: cadSubMgtCpeFilterUpstream
cadSubMgtCpeFilterUpstream.description: This is the per-CPE equivalent of docsSubMgtSubFilterUpstream

cadSubMgtCpeCpeType.name: cadSubMgtCpeCpeType
cadSubMgtCpeCpeType.description: This is the equivalent of docsSubMgtCpeType

cadSubMgtCpeIpAddrType.name: cadSubMgtCpeIpAddrType
cadSubMgtCpeIpAddrType.description: The IP address type for this CPE.

cadSubMgtCmFilterEntry.name: cadSubMgtCmFilterEntry
cadSubMgtCmFilterEntry.description: An entry in the cadSubMgtCmFilterTable. The index is the specific modem we're referring to.

cadTpFdbIfIndex.name: cadTpFdbIfIndex
cadTpFdbIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the bridge port this MAC address was learned on. For ECard ports, this is the ifIndex of eport itself. However, for DCard ports, this is the ifIndex of the DOCSIS MacLayer (ifType=127). IfIndices of types 128 (DOCSIS downstream port) and 129 (DOCSIS upstream port) should not be used in this table.

cadIfQosProfileLookupIndex.name: cadIfQosProfileLookupIndex
cadIfQosProfileLookupIndex.description: This should be 1 if this is the default flow.

cadIfQosProfileLookupRefCount.name: cadIfQosProfileLookupRefCount
cadIfQosProfileLookupRefCount.description: The number of cadIfCmtsServiceEntry rows that have the same cadIfQosProf values. If this count reaches zero(0), this row should be deleted.

cadCmtsCmStatusNumOther.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumOther
cadCmtsCmStatusNumOther.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state other(1)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRanging.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRanging
cadCmtsCmStatusNumRanging.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state ranging(2)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangingAborted.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangingAborted
cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangingAborted.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state rangingAborted(3)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangingComplete.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangingComplete
cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangingComplete.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state rangingComplete(4)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumIpComplete.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumIpComplete
cadCmtsCmStatusNumIpComplete.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state ipComplete(5)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistrationComplete.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistrationComplete
cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistrationComplete.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state registrationComplete(6)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumAccessDenied.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumAccessDenied
cadCmtsCmStatusNumAccessDenied.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state accessDenied(7)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangFlaps.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangFlaps
cadCmtsCmStatusNumRangFlaps.description: The number of times a CM on this upstream channel has reset in Ranging states.

cadCmtsCmStatusNumProvFlaps.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumProvFlaps
cadCmtsCmStatusNumProvFlaps.description: The number of times a CM on this upstream channel has reset in Provisioning states.

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegFlaps.description: The number of times a CM on this upstream channel has reset in Registered state.

cadCmtsCmStatusNumOperational.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumOperational
cadCmtsCmStatusNumOperational.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state operational(8) - deprecated

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegisteredBpiInitializ.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegisteredBpiInitializing
cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegisteredBpiInitializ.description: The number of modems on this upstream channel in state RegisteredBpiInitializing(9)

cadCmtsCmStatusNumTotal.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumTotal
cadCmtsCmStatusNumTotal.description: The total count of cable modems on this upstream channel.

cadCmtsCmStatusNumActive.description: The count of cable modems that are active. Active cable modems are recognized by the docsIfCmtsCmStatusValue other than other(1).

cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistered.name: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistered
cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistered.description: The count of cable modems that are registered and online on this upstream. Registered cable modems are those included in the counts: cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegistrationComplete, cadCmtsCmStatusNumOperational and cadCmtsCmStatusNumRegisteredBpiInitializing.

cadArpTable.name: cadArpTable
cadArpTable.description: The ARP table. It can easily used for mapping from IP addresses to physical addresses.

cadArpEntry.name: cadArpEntry
cadArpEntry.description: Each entry contains one IpAddress to MAC address equivalence.

cadArpIfIndex.name: cadArpIfIndex
cadArpIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IF-MIB's ifIndex.

cadArpAddressType.name: cadArpAddressType
cadArpAddressType.description: The IP address type for this MAC to IP address entry router interface.

cadArpNetAddress.name: cadArpNetAddress
cadArpNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the media-dependent 'physical' address.

cadArpMacAddress.name: cadArpMacAddress
cadArpMacAddress.description: The 'physical' address associated with this IP address.

cadArpType.name: cadArpType
cadArpType.description: The type of mapping. See IpNetToPhysicalType in the IP-MIB for a description.

cadArpState.name: cadArpState
cadArpState.description: The state of the mapping. See ipNetToPhysicalState in the IP-MIB for a description.

cadArpL3IfIndex.name: cadArpL3IfIndex
cadArpL3IfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IF-MIB's ifIndex.

cadMacClearFlapCounts.name: cadMacClearFlapCounts
cadMacClearFlapCounts.description: This variable always returns false(2) upon reading. When set to true(1), the flap counts in the Mac Mib are cleared.

cadMacResetCMMacAddress.name: cadMacResetCMMacAddress
cadMacResetCMMacAddress.description: This variable always returns 00:00:00:00:00:00 upon reading. When set to any other value, an attempt is made to find the Cable Modem whose MAC address matches that value and then reset that Cable Modem.

cadMacDeleteMacAddress.name: cadMacDeleteMacAddress
cadMacDeleteMacAddress.description: This variable always returns 00:00:00:00:00:00 upon reading. When set to any other value, an attempt is made to find the device whose MAC address matches that value and remove all data pertaining to that device from the CMTS.

cadMacClearDenyCounts.name: cadMacClearDenyCounts
cadMacClearDenyCounts.description: This variable always returns false(2) upon reading. When set to true(1), the counts in the modem deny status table are cleared.

cadMacClearDenyCountMacAddr.name: cadMacClearDenyCountMacAddr
cadMacClearDenyCountMacAddr.description: This variable always returns 00:00:00:00:00:00 upon reading. When set to any other value, the count in the modem deny status table whose MAC address matches that value is cleared.

cadMacClearFlapCountMacAddr.name: cadMacClearFlapCountMacAddr
cadMacClearFlapCountMacAddr.description: This variable always returns 00:00:00:00:00:00 upon reading. When set to any other value, the the modem flap count in cadIfCmtsCmStatusTable whose MAC address matches that value is cleared.

cadMacRecalculateCmSummaryIfIndex.name: cadMacRecalculateCmSummaryIfIndex
cadMacRecalculateCmSummaryIfIndex.description: This variable always returns 0 upon reading. When set to an ifIndex of a cable MAC domain, the modem summary count of the MAC domain will be recalculated.

cadMacClearFlapCountsByIfIndex.name: cadMacClearFlapCountsByIfIndex
cadMacClearFlapCountsByIfIndex.description: This variable always returns 0 upon reading. When set to an ifIndex of a cable MAC domain, the flap counts of the MAC domain will be cleared.

cadMacClearPenaltyCounts.name: cadMacClearPenaltyCounts
cadMacClearPenaltyCounts.description: This variable always returns false(2) upon reading. When set to true(1), the CM penalty counts in the cadIfCmtsCmStatusTable and the per penalty rule counts in cadEnforceRuleCountsTable are cleared.

cadMacClearPenaltyCountsByIfIndex.name: cadMacClearPenaltyCountsByIfIndex
cadMacClearPenaltyCountsByIfIndex.description: This variable always returns 0 upon reading. When set to an ifIndex of a cable MAC domain, the modem penalty count in cadIfCmtsCmStatusTable for all CMs in the MAC domain will be cleared.

cadMacClearPenaltyCountMacAddr.name: cadMacClearPenaltyCountMacAddr
cadMacClearPenaltyCountMacAddr.description: This variable always returns 00:00:00:00:00:00 upon reading. When set to any other value, the modem penalty count in cadIfCmtsCmStatusTable whose MAC address matches that value is cleared.

cadMacClearPenaltyCountScn.name: cadMacClearPenaltyCountScn
cadMacClearPenaltyCountScn.description: This variable always returns a single blank character upon reading. When set to any other value, the enforce rule penalty count in cadEnforceRuleCountsTable whose SCN matches that value is cleared.

cadQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowTable.name: cadQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowTable
cadQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowTable.description: This table provide for referencing the service flows associated with a particular cable modem. This allows for indexing into other docsQos tables that are indexed by service flow ID and ifIndex.

cadQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowEntry.name: cadQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowEntry
cadQosCmtsMacToSrvFlowEntry.description: An entry is created by CMTS for each service flow connected to this CMTS.

cadQosCmtsCmMac.name: cadQosCmtsCmMac
cadQosCmtsCmMac.description: The MAC address for the referenced CM.

cadQosCmtsServiceFlowId.name: cadQosCmtsServiceFlowId
cadQosCmtsServiceFlowId.description: An index assigned to a service flow by CMTS.

cadQosCmtsIfIndex.name: cadQosCmtsIfIndex
cadQosCmtsIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of ifType docsCableMacLayter(127) on the CMTS that is connected to the Cable Modem.

cadQosServiceClassTable.name: cadQosServiceClassTable
cadQosServiceClassTable.description: This table extends the docQosServiceClassTable and adds 1 object which is the peak traffic rate shaped to while traffic still conforms to the policing parameters.

cadQosServiceClassPeakTrafficRate.name: cadQosServiceClassPeakTrafficRate
cadQosServiceClassPeakTrafficRate.description: Peak traffic rate shaped to while traffic still conforms to the policing parameters (Tmax and Burst). If the peak rate is set to a value greater than Tmax, then the traffic will be shaped to the peak rate until the traffic is non-conforming to the policing parameters (Tmax and Burst), and then the traffic will be shaped to the Tmax rate. If the peak rate is less than the Tmax for a flow, then all traffic for that flow will shaped to the Tmax rate, regardless of the Burst parameter. Setting the peak rate to a value of 0 will result no peak rate limiting and flows having virtually unlimited bandwidth until their burst size is used up.

cadQosServiceClassLatencyControlledFlowF.name: cadQosServiceClassLatencyControlledFlowFlag
cadQosServiceClassLatencyControlledFlowF.description: This object indicated whether the flow should be should be latency-controlled. If this flag is not true than the legacy (bitrate-based) scheduler will be used.

cadCmtsCmVendorTable.name: cadCmtsCmVendorTable
cadCmtsCmVendorTable.description: The table of known and configured cable modem vendors as identified by the first three bytes of their MAC address, also known as the OUI

cadCmtsCmVendorEntry.name: cadCmtsCmVendorEntry
cadCmtsCmVendorEntry.description: Each row contains an OUI-to-vendor association

cadCmtsCmVendorName.name: cadCmtsCmVendorName

cadCmDenyMacAddress.name: cadCmDenyMacAddress
cadCmDenyMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the CM that is denied for any traffic.

cadCmDenyRowStatus.name: cadCmDenyRowStatus
cadCmDenyRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. To create a row in this table, set this object to createAndGo(4). Support of the values includes createAndGo(4) and destroy(6)

cadCmDenyStatusTable.name: cadCmDenyStatusTable

cadCmDenyStatusEntry.name: cadCmDenyStatusEntry
cadCmDenyStatusEntry.description: Entry of cable modem deny status.

cadCmDenyAttempts.name: cadCmDenyAttempts

cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterTable.name: cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterTable
cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterTable.reference: DOCSIS 3.0 MAC and Upper Layer Protocols Interface Specification CM-SP-MULPIv3.0-I05-07mmdd, Service Flow SID Cluster Assignments section in the Common Radio Frequency Interface Encodings Annex.
cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterTable.description: This object defines the SID clusters associated with an upstream service flow.

cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterEntry.name: cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterEntry
cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterEntry.description: The conceptual row of cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterTable. The ifIndex key corresponds to the MAC Domain interface of the service flow. The index scheme used upstream channel ifIndex intead of channel ID to speed up query performance.

cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterChIfIndex.name: cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterChIfIndex
cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterChIfIndex.description: This key represents the upstream Channel ifIndex mapped to the corresponding SID.

cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterUcid.name: cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterUcid
cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterUcid.description: This attribute represents the UCID assigned to the upstream channel in this SID Cluster.

cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterSid.name: cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterSid
cadQosServiceFlowSidClusterSid.description: This attribute represents the SID assigned to the upstream channel in this SID Cluster.

cadQosServiceFlowSegHdr.name: cadQosServiceFlowSegHdr
cadQosServiceFlowSegHdr.description: This object indicates the segment header in a MTCM enabled flow is on or off.

cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpTable.name: cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpTable
cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpTable.description: This table provides a SNMP style wrapper to the MAC DB with a direct translation from MAC to the IP address and CM MAC associated with the CM or CPE MAC.

cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpEntry.name: cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpEntry
cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpEntry.description: Per MAC information stored in MAC DB

cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddrType.name: cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddrType
cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddrType.description: Inet Ip address type (IPv4 or IPv6)associated with this CM or CPE MAC address.

cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddr.name: cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddr
cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpAddr.description: Inet Ip address (IPv4 or IPv6)associated with this CM or CPE MAC address.

cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpCmMacAddr.name: cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpCmMacAddr
cadIfCmtsMacToInetIpCmMacAddr.description: Mac address of the CM associated with the MAC address. If this is an entry for a CM, the it will be the same as the cadIfCmtsmac. For a CPE MAC, this will be the MAC address of the CM.

cadEnforceRuleTableLastChange.name: cadEnforceRuleTableLastChange
cadEnforceRuleTableLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which a row in the cadEnforceRuleTable was added or deleted. Is zero if not modified since last boot.

cadEnforceRuleTable.name: cadEnforceRuleTable
cadEnforceRuleTable.description: This object describes an enforce rule list For the Integrated SC Agility feature on a CMTS. Each object instance defines an enforce rule.

cadEnforceRuleReferenceSCN.name: cadEnforceRuleReferenceSCN
cadEnforceRuleReferenceSCN.description: This attribute represents the Service Class Name from which the reference parameter set values for a SF were derived. This ASCII string acts as a handle pointing to the Service Class Name In the docsQosParamSetTable. This SCN's name and pre-configured QoS parameters are used to determine if a particular Service Flow should be mapped into this particular Enforce Rule.

cadEnforceRuleEnforceSCN.name: cadEnforceRuleEnforceSCN
cadEnforceRuleEnforceSCN.description: This attribute represents the Service Class Name from which the penalty parameter set values are derived. Must be specified. This ASCII string acts as a handle pointing to the Service Class Name In the docsQosParamSetTable. This SCN's pre-configured QoS parameters for Priority, Tmax, Tpeak, and Max Burst are used to temporarily over-write the service flow's QoS Parameter Set values whenever that service flow bandwidth exceeds the threshold.

cadEnforceRuleAvgBwRateUsageTrigger.name: cadEnforceRuleAvgBwRateUsageTrigger
cadEnforceRuleAvgBwRateUsageTrigger.description: The threshold bandwidth (in kilobits per second) above which the service flow is identified as being a Heavy User below which the service flow is identified as being a Light User. This must be specified.

cadEnforceRuleAvgHistoryDuration.name: cadEnforceRuleAvgHistoryDuration
cadEnforceRuleAvgHistoryDuration.description: The duration of time (in minutes) that is used to monitor and calculate the average bandwidth for each service flow associated with this Enforce Rule. In essence, we will use a sliding window with a duration specified by this parameter whenever calculating the average bandwidth that the service flow has utilized. Values must be divisible by 30. The history duration must be an integer multiple of the sampling interval.

cadEnforceRuleSamplingInterval.name: cadEnforceRuleSamplingInterval
cadEnforceRuleSamplingInterval.description: The period of time (in minutes) between successive slides of the sliding window. It is also the temporal distance over which the sliding window is moved whenever it is slid. The penalty duration and window duration must be an integer multiple of the sampling interval.

cadEnforceRulePenaltyDuration.name: cadEnforceRulePenaltyDuration
cadEnforceRulePenaltyDuration.description: The duration of time (in minutes) that a monitored service flow is held in the penalty box after it has been found to be a Heavy User. Being placed in the penalty box implies that the service flow has had its Priority, Tmax, Tpeak, and Max Burst parameters within its QoS Parameter Set overridden by the corresponding values from the Enforce Service Class Name. Values must be divisible by 30. The penalty duration must be an integer multiple of the sampling interval.

cadEnforceRuleCreateTime.name: cadEnforceRuleCreateTime
cadEnforceRuleCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime in seconds when this rule was created. Set to new sysUpTime if created before last boot.

cadEnforceRuleStatus.name: cadEnforceRuleStatus
cadEnforceRuleStatus.description: The conceptual row status of this object.

cadEnforceRuleCountsTable.name: cadEnforceRuleCountsTable
cadEnforceRuleCountsTable.description: This object contains the number of times an enforce rule has been used to penalize a service flow.

cadEnforceRuleCountsPenalties.name: cadEnforceRuleCountsPenalties
cadEnforceRuleCountsPenalties.description: Number of times the CM has had a SF penalized by this Enforce Rule.

cadQosServiceClassControlTable.name: cadQosServiceClassControlTable
cadQosServiceClassControlTable.description: This table extends the docQosServiceClassTable and adds control features for service classes.

cadQosServiceClassControlEntry.name: cadQosServiceClassControlEntry
cadQosServiceClassControlEntry.description: This is an extension of the DocsQosServiceClassEntry table that provides additional service class control features.

cadQosServiceClassControlSendDsc.name: cadQosServiceClassControlSendDsc
cadQosServiceClassControlSendDsc.description: This variable always returns false(2) upon reading. When set to true(1), a DSC updating the SF parameters is sent to all CMs having a SF matching this SCN name and whose QOS parameter set is out-of-date.

cadQosServiceClassControlSendDscLastUpda.name: cadQosServiceClassControlSendDscLastUpdated
cadQosServiceClassControlSendDscLastUpda.description: The time that cadQosServiceClassControlSendDsc was written for this row. If it was updated prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value. Used to decide if a DSC is needed for a SF using this SCN.

cadQosServiceClassCmControlTable.name: cadQosServiceClassCmControlTable
cadQosServiceClassCmControlTable.description: This table extends the docQosServiceClassTable and adds a per-CM control feature for service classes.

cadQosServiceClassCmControlEntry.name: cadQosServiceClassCmControlEntry
cadQosServiceClassCmControlEntry.description: This is an extension of the DocsQosServiceClassEntry table that provides additional service class control features.

cadQosServiceClassCmControlSendDscMacAdd.name: cadQosServiceClassCmControlSendDscMacAddr
cadQosServiceClassCmControlSendDscMacAdd.description: This variable always returns 00:00:00:00:00:00 upon reading. When set to any other value, a DSC updating the SF parameters in the CM whose MAC address matches the value written is sent, providing that there is a SF matching this SCN's name, and the CM's QoS parameter set for that SF is out-of-date.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusTable.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusTable
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusTable.description: This table contains DOCSIS 3.1 CM Capabilities from CM registration requests.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusEntry.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusEntry
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusEntry.description: An entry has the capabilities from the registration request for one CM.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusMacAddress.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusMacAddress
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the modem.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusOkOfdmMod.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusOkOfdmMod
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusOkOfdmMod.description: The OFDM modulations supported by the CM, as reported in TLV 5.52. QAM8 and QAM32 are not allowed for DS channels.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusOkOfdmaMod.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusOkOfdmaMod
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusOkOfdmaMod.description: The OFDMA US modulations supported by the CM, as reported in TLV 5.53.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusDsLowFreq.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusDsLowFreq
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusDsLowFreq.description: The low DS edge frequency (Downstream Lower Band Edge) supported by the CM,as reported in TLV 5.54.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusDsHighFreq.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusDsHighFreq
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusDsHighFreq.description: The high DS edge frequency (Downstream Upper Band Edge) supported by the CM, as reported in TLV 5.55.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusUsHighFreq.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusUsHighFreq
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmStatusUsHighFreq.description: The high US edge frequency (Diplexor Upper Band Edge) supported by the CM,as reported in TLV 5.56.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfTable.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfTable
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfTable.description: This table contains the OFDM and OFDMA channels and profiles assigned to DOCSIS 3.1 CMs, and their status.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfEntry.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfEntry
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfEntry.description: An entry describes one channel and profile assigned to a DOCSIS 3.1 CM.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfMacAddress.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfMacAddress
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the modem.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfIfIndex.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfIfIndex
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an OFDM DS or OFDMA US channel.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfProfId.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfProfId
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfProfId.description: The profile number plus one of this profile for a DS channel. The data IUC number for a US channel. Range is (1..16|256) for downstream channels, and (5|6|9|10|11|12|13) for upstream channels.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfDirection.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfDirection
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfDirection.description: Whether the channel is downstream or upstream.

cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfStatus.name: cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfStatus
cadIfCmtsCmOfdmProfStatus.description: Active if there are no issues for this profile for this CM on this channel. Impaired when we receive a CM-STATUS message of type ofdmProfileFailure, for OFDM channels, or due to excessive errors seen by the receiver, for OFDMA channels.

cadSubmgtFilterGrpDescTable.name: cadSubmgtFilterGrpDescTable
cadSubmgtFilterGrpDescTable.description: Each entry of this table defines the description text associated with a single subscriber management filter group. The object exists independent of the existence of the particular filter group (docsSubmgt3FilterGrpTable (DOCS-SUBMGT3-MIB))

cadSubmgtFilterGrpId.name: cadSubmgtFilterGrpId
cadSubmgtFilterGrpId.description: This key is an identifier for a set of classifiers known as a filter group. Each CM may be associated with several filter groups for its upstream and downstream traffic, one group per target end point on the CM as defined in the docsSubmgt3GrpEntry object (DOCS-SUBMGT3-MIB). Typically, many CMs share a common set of filter groups.

cadSubmgtFilterGrpDescription.name: cadSubmgtFilterGrpDescription
cadSubmgtFilterGrpDescription.description: A user-defined description of the filter group (1 to 32 human- readable characters).

cadSubmgtFilterGrpRowStatus.name: cadSubmgtFilterGrpRowStatus
cadSubmgtFilterGrpRowStatus.description: Control object for row creation and deletion. Support limited to active(1), createAndGo(4), destroy(6).
